Teriyaki Chicken, one of my favorite & easy dishes. 🫶🏼

If you can marinate the chicken the day before do it! (Just saves you time) 

•2pks of Chicken tenders or chicken breast. Cut into small bite pieces. 

For the teriyaki sauce, in a small bowl add the following:
•1/2 cup of Soy Sauce
•1/4 cup of Brown Sugar 
•1tbsp of Sesame oil
•1 tsp Ginger grated
•1 tsp Garlic grated 
•Fry on high heat the meat until it starts getting a little brown.
•Then add the Teriyaki Sauce, give a mix and cook on medium heat for 3-4 mins till the sauce is absorbed and coats the chicken pieces.
•Then BAM! Add some white rice, boil some broccoli for 5mins, then top off with the sesame seeds or chopped spring onion greens. 

Enjoy 😛

Need tips on how to put fake lashes? I got you covered sis. 🫶🏼 I know how tricky it can be putting them on, but with my tips you’re going to be putting them on like a pro! I hope this works for you and if it does please let me know. What should I film next? 🤩

Step 1: Measure your lashes 
Step 2: Trim to your size 
Step 3: Apply even layer of glue (don’t forget corners) 
Step 4: important!! Wait 30secs to a minute the most.
Step 5: Look down at your mirror!!! 
Step 6: Apply in the center then corners.
BAM!!! Apply little bit of pressure, mascara and you’re ready to go! You have applied your falsies! 💓

Hey guyzzzz! I thought I could re-introduced myself to any new faces here. 💓 My name is Jessica Gonzalez, I am a Mexican American from Dallas Texas. 🇲🇽🇺🇸 I’m going to be 28 years old on May 1st. I’m the youngest of three in my family. My favorite colors are green and pink. I like playing videos games. Im scared of bees lol. I’m going to turn a year married to the love of my life, Kevin. Annnnd we recently became homeowners. ❤️

I work part-time at a dental office as front desk, dental assistant and office manager. Yes I do it all lol 🦷🪥 I’ve been balancing dentistry and makeup for the past 10 years. My goal is to be an influencer and a makeup artist full-time. Beauty has always been my passion since I was a little girl. I remember watching my mom and my sister do their makeup and seeing all the glamour that comes with being a woman. From nails, outfits, heels, sparkly jewelry, etc. 

As mentioned, I’ve been doing makeup for about 10 years now and I wouldn’t change it for the world. I remember being so confused and lost after high school. I didn’t know what career I wanted to follow. Also, I was in a really dark phase in my life at the time and makeup was just my escape. It brought the light, the happiness and the courage out of me. That’s when I knew that the beauty industry was for me. 🥹

And now, I'm here I am on social media with a great platform, able to do what I love, all thanks to you guys. Thank you for your support. I hope you continue following me with this journey and see where it goes. Love y'all💓
Happy Easter from Mr. & Mrs. Iraheta 🐰

Today was the end of a big chapter. 🦷 My last day as a front desk & dental assistant. I’ve been waiting for this moment for so long. Dentistry was and always will be a big impact in my life. It has taught me many things, and given me many opportunities, and I’ll always be grateful for that. When I graduated high school I was unsure of what I wanted to do. What path I wanted to follow. I honestly felt like I didn’t have a purpose. But I remember telling my 19 year old self whatever I end up doing, I’m gonna make sure it makes me happy. Eventually I found my purpose and my happiness which is makeup. The beauty industry, physically and mentally helped me. It brought out the light in the darkness, made me come out of my shell, and it made my confidence grow like no other. 

Throughout the years of doing makeup, I’ve gained a great following, and I want to thank every single one of you for supporting me for so long. Not only did I post makeup, but I made great friends along the way. You all are so appreciated in my heart. All your comments, replies, likes. I see it all and I truly appreciate it. I hope you continue to support me in this new chapter in my life of doing this full-time. I’ve worked so hard to get here and Im just so happy, excited and relieved. I hope I inspire someone who has a hobby or a passion to go for it. Chase your dreams. Don’t let anything or anyone stop you. You can do it. It may be difficult at first, but you will get there. Life is so precious so just do what you love. And live your life to the fullest. 

Biggest thank you to all my family & friends. To my amazing husband for being my #1 supporter through this whole thing. He has helped me so much to get here and I couldn’t have done it without him. I never thought I’d get here so thank you again to every single one of you for making this possible. I love you so much. Thank you thank you thank you. -Jess 💕

Must haves and why? Let me tell ya sis 👛

•Wallet: we obviously have to take our drivers license with us everywhere for safety and the drinksssss hehe. Also to swipe my husband’s card bc I deserve it 😮‍💨

•Gum: girrrrrrl I always carry gum. I don’t like having bad breath. Also, it’s for when I’m really full. I stay having gum. Always lol. That or mints! 

•My pressed powder: I take my Mac Studio fix powder everywhere I go. One I feel like I just need a mirror with me (to check if there’s anything in my teeth) and then two I usually always retouch my makeup. So yes I’m that girl retouching her makeup and gloss. Periodttttt ✨

•Lip Pencil and Gloss: now the lip pencil is one of my favorites it’s from @colourpopcosmetics in the color 951. I always carry it to retouch my lipstick combo. And you guys know I’ve been recently loving the @elfcosmetics lip boil but it’s usually any gloss or lipstick of what I decide to put that day. 💄 

•Lash Glue: so this is mainly for my sake, but also others. I always like to carry lash glue, even when I’m not wearing lashes. I like to look out for my queens. I’ve come across emergencies with friends or girls in the restroom where their eyelashes are falling off and I usually come to the rescue so I just like carrying it for emergencies. 😂🫶🏼

•Aquaphor: I know I have my lipstick combo, but theres moments where I just want a regular Chapstick and this is it. I love my @aquaphorus 💙

Roasted Tomato Soup! This was sooooo yummy and comforting, especially in this cold weather. 🥰 I followed @tiniyounger recipe on TikTok, I love all her videos 🫶🏼

 R E C I P E 
10-12 tomatoes (enough for 2-3 servings)
2 bulk garlic 🧄 
1 chopped onion 🧅 
Basil stems 
Olive oil
Splash of balsamic vinegar 
Salt
Pepper
Paprika 
Then into the oven at 400 degrees for 45 minutes orrrr until nice and roasted. 
Add to blender 
1 cup of vegetable broth 
Half a cup of heavy cream 
Basil leafs 
Oregano
Chili pepper flakes 
Blend then add to a pot, you can strain it! I didn’t tho, it’s just optional :) 
Top it off with parmesan or shredded cheese. 
Then serve with grilled cheese, bread, garlic bread, etc. 
enjoyyyyyyyy 😍🤤
